import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About" description="About this site.">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>This site is an automated, daily-refreshed comparison of VPS and cloud hosting providers built for developers who want a quick, side-by-side view of pricing and specs.</p>
  <h2>How the data is collected</h2>
  <p>Pricing data is pulled from each provider's public API or pricing page once a day via a GitHub Actions cron job. Each provider has a dedicated fetcher script in <code>scripts/</code>. When a live source is unreachable the previous good data is preserved, so the site never goes blank.</p>
  <h2>How the site is built</h2>
  <p>Every page on this site is statically generated by Astro and deployed to GitHub Pages. There is no database and no server-side rendering. New articles are drafted weekly by the Anthropic Claude API and committed back to the repo.</p>
  <h2>How we make money</h2>
  <p>Outbound provider links are referral links. We earn a commission when you sign up for a paid plan through them. This does not affect rankings, which are derived purely from public pricing data.</p>
</Base>
